Subject: [PATCH] newlib: rename libm_a- prefix to a- in MATHOBJS_IN_LIBC

newlib 4.4.0's Makefile.am declares MATHOBJS_IN_LIBC with
`libm_a-` object-name prefix, matching the output older automake
produced from per-target CFLAGS on a static `.a` library.  Modern
automake (tested with 1.18.1) canonicalizes the prefix to just
`a-`, so the compile rules produce `libm/common/a-s_fpclassify.o`
etc.  MATHOBJS_IN_LIBC still says `libm_a-s_fpclassify.o`, so the
stamp-libc-math-objects extraction rule fails to find anything in
libm.a, and the subsequent libc.a assembly fails with:

    ar: libc/libm_a-s_fpclassify.o: No such file or directory

Rename every entry in MATHOBJS_IN_LIBC from the `libm_a-` prefix to
`a-` so the list matches what the compile rules actually produce.
No other uses of `libm_a-` appear in Makefile.am.

diff --git a/newlib/Makefile.am b/newlib/Makefile.am
--- a/newlib/Makefile.am
+++ b/newlib/Makefile.am
@@ -113,19 +113,19 @@
 # both libc.a and libm.a.  We build them in libm.a and copy them over,
 # along with some required supporting routines.
 MATHOBJS_IN_LIBC = \
-	libm_a-s_fpclassify.o libm_a-sf_fpclassify.o \
-	libm_a-s_isinf.o libm_a-sf_isinf.o \
-	libm_a-s_isnan.o libm_a-sf_isnan.o \
-	libm_a-s_isinfd.o libm_a-sf_isinff.o \
-	libm_a-s_isnand.o libm_a-sf_isnanf.o \
-	libm_a-s_nan.o libm_a-sf_nan.o \
-	libm_a-s_ldexp.o libm_a-sf_ldexp.o \
-	libm_a-s_frexp.o libm_a-sf_frexp.o libm_a-frexpl.o \
-	libm_a-s_modf.o \
-	libm_a-sf_modf.o libm_a-s_scalbn.o \
-	libm_a-sf_scalbn.o \
-	libm_a-s_finite.o libm_a-sf_finite.o \
-	libm_a-s_copysign.o libm_a-sf_copysign.o
+	a-s_fpclassify.o a-sf_fpclassify.o \
+	a-s_isinf.o a-sf_isinf.o \
+	a-s_isnan.o a-sf_isnan.o \
+	a-s_isinfd.o a-sf_isinff.o \
+	a-s_isnand.o a-sf_isnanf.o \
+	a-s_nan.o a-sf_nan.o \
+	a-s_ldexp.o a-sf_ldexp.o \
+	a-s_frexp.o a-sf_frexp.o a-frexpl.o \
+	a-s_modf.o \
+	a-sf_modf.o a-s_scalbn.o \
+	a-sf_scalbn.o \
+	a-s_finite.o a-sf_finite.o \
+	a-s_copysign.o a-sf_copysign.o

 ## Place the libm_a objects in libc/ to keep the top dir tidy.
 stamp-libc-math-objects: libm.a
